spanGrp.span: OK its the thirty first of the seventh twenty seventeen with Alice Toka working on the red yam story board of the MelaTAMP project in Ranvetlam village in the Fanbyak language.
Rose, Youkon are friends with Mary and Lising
Ros, Youkon lor e bilbilen mane Meri mo Lising
they went, they were going the garden
lir van, tu lir van lonōr
they went and stayed in the gardenm they were workin in the garden
tir van so lonōr, tu lir kee lonōr
tir - mistake should be 'tu lir' or just 'lir'
they went and were just resting
lir van tu lir geb ngaab
double check meaning of geb and ngaab
went, Youkon already stood up and was returning to the garden
van Youkon bur tetaala te kolili van lonōr
Ros too sat, stood up and was returning to the garden
Ros mōn tetaa, tetaala tu tokolili van lonōr
Lising and Mary too they returned to the garden
Lising mane Meri mōn lor kolili van lonōr
searched for her yam which, her red yam which was missing
tu kulone an rom go tese, an rom filfili go teselaal
she asked, Mary asked Lising, "who ate my yam?"
tuusi, Meri tuusi Lising, "Si nge maane ak rom?"
sounds like tile rather than tigile
Mary said, "It's not Rose, but Youkon I think"
Meri tigile, "Tolo e Ros, rō Youkon ben"
Lising said to Mary, "you just look at their teeth, Youkon's teeth'
Lising tigile vane Meri, "etu ob sese luol, luo Youkon nga"
"If her teeth are red, then it is Youkon who ate your yam"
"on e luon abififili, a youkon go maane am rom"
Mary saw Youkon, she was really cross
Mere tese Youkon lon tisili go lon tisili
when she asked for the yam from Youkon, Rose laughed and laughed
one tutuusi rom mane Youkon, rō Ros tu teman go tu teman
Youkon i bin kakae, i askem Youkon nao
Youkon ate it, she asks Youkon now
hem i stat blo laf nao
she is starting to laugh now
Mary spoke, she was asking Youkon and Ros was laughing lots
mu, Meri tu te werwaar, tu tuusi Youkon rō Ros tu teman go tu teman
Lising was pointing to Rose, as Rose ate her yam
Lising tu tusune Ros, gile Ros nge maane an rom
she said that "it isn't Youkon, but Rose"
tigile go "tolo e Youkon, rō Ros"
I no Youkon hem i Ros
"it wasn't Youkon, but Rose who ate your yam"
"tolo e Youkon, rō Ros nge maane am rom"
